basichero.heading: Business Waste Compactors
basichero.body: Our network of technicians and extensive equipment inventory are prepared to handle whatever waste compaction challenges you have.

singlecolumntext.heading: Compactor Solutions
singlecolumntext.body:
We provide compaction equipment to help you maximize cost savings and increase hauling efficiency for dry, wet, bulky or mixed waste streams.

Our inventory of new and reconditioned equipment combined with industry expertise and excellent customer service will help you optimize disposal for your business.

data.dc:title: Compactor Solutions
data.dc:description:
We provide compaction equipment to help you maximize cost savings and increase hauling efficiency for dry, wet, bulky or mixed waste streams.

Our inventory of new and reconditioned equipment combined with industry expertise and excellent customer service will help you optimize disposal for your business.

multimedia.heading: A Compactor for Every Industry
multimedia.body:
With a wide range of equipment and purchase or rental options, we can design a solution that works for you.

We have compactors for dry and wet waste streams, recyclables, space-restricted areas and specialty disposal circumstances.

Through our SmartEnergy℠ compactor, we also offer technology that reduces electricity consumption by up to 70% while maintaining performance compared to traditional compactors.
multimedia.imageAltText: Waste Management SmartEnergy solar powered trash compactor.

multimedia_734374261.heading: Rentals & Purchases
multimedia_734374261.body:
Every location is unique so we coordinate a visit from a skilled technician to understand the installation requirements.

After information is collected and reviewed, we’ll recommend a machine that meets safety requirements, increases diversion rates and improves your operations.

Our comprehensive purchase program includes freight, delivery, and installation and setup.

multimedia_523779715.heading: Maintenance
multimedia_523779715.body:
In many cases, unmanaged compaction equipment without a maintenance plan can have shorter lifespan.

Our technicians can perform preventive maintenance, review your site’s condition and provide a detailed report with recommendations for next steps.

If you buy through Waste Management or own existing equipment, maintenance is available as needed or as part of a custom program.

multimedia_1336035909.heading: Repairs & Restoration
multimedia_1336035909.body:
Our experienced team is available for dispatch to help minimize downtime and maximize uptime for affected equipment.

Repair services are performed by qualified technicians with decades of field experience working with all types of compactors.

Maintenance and repair work can be added to a rental program.
multimedia_1336035909.imageAltText: A WM employee wearing a helmet and reflective vest works on a tablet while standing amongst large equipment.

multimedia_842457661.heading: Removal & Disposal
multimedia_842457661.body:
If your business has an old, unused or damaged compactor, we'll take care of it for you.

Let us know what you need and we'll send an experienced technician to your location to remove the compactor and dispose of it properly.

multimedia_1174314378.heading: Training & Support
multimedia_1174314378.body:
Regardless of your waste stream and type of equipment, we make installation seamless.

We support our customers with thorough in-person instruction and ongoing account management while the equipment is in use.

multimedia_193165358.heading: Multiple Waste Streams
multimedia_193165358.body:
Our equipment is designed to handle challenges that come with dry, wet, bulky and mixed waste streams.

When dealing with dry waste streams like paper and packaging, our compactors can reduce hauling costs by decreasing the number of pick-ups.

For wet waste streams, our watertight equipment avoids leakage, insect/rodent infestations and unsanitary conditions caused by less effective equipment.
